## FORMAT COMPLIANCE RULE
반드시 커버리지 메트릭이 포함된 테스트 보고서를 아래 네이밍 규칙에 따라 출력할 것.

## Test Generation Workflow
Trigger: `generate tests for <file/function> with coverage`

### Procedure
1. Analyze target code (inputs, outputs, edge cases, dependencies)
2. Generate mock setup for all external dependencies
3. Write unit tests for:
   - Happy path (expected input → expected output)
   - Edge cases (null, empty, boundary values)
   - Error cases (invalid input → expected error)
   - Async cases (race conditions, timeouts if applicable)
5. Run tests → measure coverage → report
6. If coverage below target: identify uncovered branches → add tests → re-measure

### Integration Test Generation
Trigger: `generate integration test for <usecase>`

1. Analyze flow (entry point → dependencies → external systems)
2. Set up test containers or in-memory DB
3. Write success path test + failure path test
4. Clean up test data (idempotent)
5. Report

### 테스트 네이밍 컨벤션
명확하고 설명적인 이름을 사용. 권장 패턴:
- `given_<조건>_when_<행동>_then_<기대결과>`
- `test_<행동>_<시나리오>_<기대결과>` — 이 패턴도 허용

테스트 이름은 검증 내용을 명확히 전달해야 함. `TestCSVErrors` 같은 클래스 단위 그룹화는 함수 수준 네이밍 없이 사용하지 말 것.

## Test Hierarchy
```
Unit → Integration → E2E → Contract
  ↓        ↓         ↓       ↓
Property  Snapshot  Visual  Chaos
```

|Layer|Goal|Key Rule|
|------|------|------|
|Unit|Coverage target (varies by scale)|Mock all external dependencies|
|Integration|All core flows|Test containers or in-memory DB|
|E2E|5-10 core user stories|Full run under 2 min|
|Contract|Service interface verification|Consumer-Driven Contract (Pact etc.)|

### Advanced Techniques
|Technique|When|
|------|------|
|Property-based|Computation/transform/serialization logic|
|Snapshot|UI components, API responses, config files|
|Visual regression|Frontend components, design systems|
|Mutation testing|Core business logic, periodic quality audits|
|Chaos engineering|Large distributed systems, high availability|

### Async Test Essentials
- Race conditions (concurrent access scenarios)
- Timeouts (async work completes within deadline)
- Deadlock detection
- Backpressure (slow consumer + fast producer)

